title.narrative: By 2021, strengthened health sector capacity for integrated MNCH service delivery

description.narrative: Through the UN Joint Programme, UNICEF supported the MoH health policy shift to target the most vulnerable populations through primary health care as an effective, efficient and sustainable approach to making further progress and achieving Universal Health Coverage. Primary Health Care is now a key priority for the 9th Health Sector Development Plan as a multi-sectoral approach for reaching Universal Health Care. Through the community health systems strengthening strategic action plan, the PHC's emphasis on community-based services is an important way to ensure access, even for rural, remote and disadvantaged populations. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
